description._content: Description: The Oil-Fields by night. Waste gas from the wells being burnt off provides the illumination. Description: Falls on the Tembi River near Tembiun. A water-mill can be seen on the right of the picture. Location: Tembiun, Persia Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/714 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
